Message:
feat(galiana): add property-based agent eval harness with CI

Implements agent evaluation infrastructure for detecting silent degradation
when prompts, model routing, or agent configurations change. Uses property-
based assertions (not exact text matching) to handle model non-determinism.

- 5 golden fixtures: sql-injection, n-plus-one, tight-coupling,
  contradictory-prd, stale-docs covering all review agent domains
- eval.py: orchestrator with property checks, baseline metrics,
  interbench scoring, regression detection (exit 0/1/2)
- utils.py: shared iter_jsonl, normalize_title, titles_match (DRY
  extraction from experiment.py + analyze.py)
- CI: daily cron (all topologies) + on-push (T4 fast check)
- analyze.py: new eval_health KPI wired into galiana dashboard
- galiana.md: eval subcommand + SKILL.md eval section

Addresses review findings: P0 precision formula (filter to P0/P1),
P1 exit code regression detection, P1 unrecognized assertion warning,
P1 metric rename (unmatched_findings), P2 input_dir validation.
